parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or acceleration
the engine light or wrench light comes on
the vehicle hesitates or stalls
the vehicle goes into "limp mode"
and the accelerator pedal feels soft or unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the power steering assist warning indicator illuminates
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates
the vehicle becomes hard to steer
the steering column fails
and the vehicle may stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure and Recall Repair Delays
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded. The delay in recall repairs can exacerbate the issue, putting drivers at risk.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while being operated at various speeds
the check engine and check fuel intake warning indicators illuminate
fuel leakage
and a strong fuel smell while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose power, decelerate independently, and stall without warning, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or acceleration
the engine RPMs increase
the vehicle decelerates independently
the vehicle stalls without warning
the wrench light or check engine warning light illuminates
the accelerator pedal has no effect
the vehicle hesitates when accelerating.
